oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: People mingling on rock
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: A side view of an assortment of people standing and sitting on Bee Rock, Monterey, Tennessee. Three girls huddle on the ground, two men explore the edge of the rock. Most of the men wear hats. Many people look like they are having conversations.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Tennessee Department of Conservation Photograph Collection, 1937-1976
